With ##delete-selection-mode## enabled, pressing Backspace while [[region|selecting text]] will delete the selected region.

It is included as of Emacs 20.1

* [[https://git.savannah.gnu.org/cgit/emacs.git/tree/lisp/delsel.el#n84 Source code]]
* [[https://www.gnu.org/software/emacs/manual/html_node/efaq/Replacing-highlighted-text.html Manual Page]]

== Usage ==

Put the following in your [[init file]]: ##(delete-selection-mode 1)##

== See Also == 

* TransientMarkMode -- Transient Mark mode is enabled in Delete Selection mode.
* [[delsel.el]] -- A modification by DrewAdams which is more compatible with ##completion-mode##.

== Footnotes ==

If you are writing EmacsLisp and want to adapt commands to ##delete-selection-mode##, see [[http://lists.gnu.org/archive/html/emacs-devel/2012-05/msg00515.html this discussion]] about the use of the ##delete-selection## [[symbol]]

In [[XEmacs]], delete-selection-mode may be called ##pending-delete-mode##

